ProtoTheorem:
. "A metric space $(A,\rho)$ is complete if and only if every 
   nested sequence $\{T_n\}$ of nonempty closed subsets of $A$ 
   such that $\lim_{n\to\infty}d(T_n)=0$ has a nonempty 
   intersection."
